1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,800
AI fact checking should not replace one black box with another.

2
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:12,000
FactRelay turns each investigation into a navigable evidence chain.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:19,500
Submit text, a public link, or a social-media screenshot.

4
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:27,000
A live run extracts the claim, then retrieves current public evidence.

5
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:33,800
We test the familiar claim that the Great Wall is visible from the Moon.

6
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:41,000
FactRelay collects evidence before calling two Gonka models in sequence.

7
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:48,500
The verdict is Refuted, with a Truth Score of 9.

8
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:58,000
The score is deterministic: model consensus plus source-weighted evidence.

9
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:07,000
Every source keeps its publisher, date, URL, stance, and reliability.

10
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Models may cite only this numbered ledger; invalid source indexes are rejected.

11
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:25,500
Kimi-K2.6 investigates and forms the first evidence-based judgment.

12
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:36,000
MiniMax-M2.7 challenges it for source laundering, chronology errors, and missing context.

13
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:44,500
Every inference preserves its upstream Gonka Request ID and execution order.

14
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:54,000
A receipt proves which call produced the analysis—not whether the claim is true.

15
00:01:54,000 --> 00:02:02,000
All semantic inference runs exclusively through GonkaRouter.

16
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Tested scoring, SSRF guards, and null preview receipts make the boundary explicit.

17
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:17,000
Verdict, Sources, Review, and Proof remain individually inspectable.

18
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:24,000
The user receives a reviewable chain—not just an answer.

19
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:30,000
FactRelay. Question the claim. Keep the receipts.
